Calling a DLL using Metaware

    This example shows how to call a Metaware 32-bit linear executable DLL
    from a Metaware 32-bit linear executable program.  The example uses the
    DOS/4G API to load the DLL using either of two methods: an IMPLIB, to
    cause the DLL to be loaded at program load time, or dynamically, using
    the DOS/4G D32LoadModule API call.
     
    The example consists of the folllowing files in the EXAMPLES\DLL\
    METAWARE directory:
    
    MYDLL.C     C source file for DLL example code.  To be called from
                CALLER.C

    MYDLL.DEF   Standard DEF file for exporting MYDLL functions

    CALLER.C    C source file for calling DLL functions in MYDLL

    CALLER.DEF  Standard DEF file for importing MYDLL functions

    MAKEFILE    Polymake-configured makefile to build all the example
                executables using Metware  
